for 20 days.

00:02:52.880 --> 00:02:54.735
And then on the 21st day
her balance would

00:02:54.735 --> 00:02:55.790
have gone to $300.

00:02:55.790 --> 00:02:59.500
So the average is going to be
equal to $600-- she had a $600

00:02:59.500 --> 00:03:02.200
balance for the first 20 days.

00:03:02.200 --> 00:03:07.610
Times 20 plus 300 times
the remainder days.

00:03:07.610 --> 00:03:09.315
So 300 for 10 days.

00:03:09.315 --> 00:03:12.310
And that's all divided by
the number of days.

00:03:12.310 --> 00:03:14.750
So statement one, alone, is
