00:04:35.730 --> 00:04:43.070
If x is an integer, they're
asking is 9 to the x plus 9 to

00:04:43.070 --> 00:04:48.150
the minus x equal to b?

00:04:48.150 --> 00:04:49.760
Who knows?

00:04:49.760 --> 00:04:58.800
Problem one says 3 to the x plus
3 to the minus x is equal

00:04:58.800 --> 00:05:02.450
to the square root
of b plus 2.

00:05:02.450 --> 00:05:04.560
So right from the get-go I don't
see-- I mean there's 3's

00:05:04.560 --> 00:05:07.170
there's 9's, there seems to
be some relationship.

00:05:07.170 --> 00:05:09.890
Let's square both sides of this
equation, see if it can

00:05:09.890 --> 00:05:12.180
reduce to something that's
useful here.

00:05:12.180 --> 00:05:13.510
So the right hand
side is easy.

00:05:13.510 --> 00:05:19.020
The left hand side, if you
square it you get 3 to the 2x.

00:05:19.020 --> 00:05:22.910
And then you get plus
2 times these

00:05:22.910 --> 00:05:24.210
multiplied by each other.

00:05:24.210 --> 00:05:32.650
3 to the x, 3 to the minus x
plus 3 to the minus 2x is

00:05:32.650 --> 00:05:34.940
equal to b plus 2.

00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:36.730
I just squared both sides.

00:05:36.730 --> 00:05:39.190
3 to the x times 3 to
the minus x, that

00:05:39.190 --> 00:05:41.890
just equals 1, right?

00:05:41.890 --> 00:05:43.970
You could add the exponents,
that's equal to 3 to the 0.

00:05:43.970 --> 00:05:44.630
That equals 1.

00:05:44.630 --> 00:05:46.750
Or you could view that as 3 to
the x divided by 3 to the x.

00:05:46.750 --> 00:05:49.060
Either way, that equals 1.

00:05:49.060 --> 00:05:51.335
Then you're left with 2 on both
sides of the equation.

00:05:51.335 --> 00:05:53.970
So you can get rid of that.

00:05:53.970 --> 00:06:00.870
So then we're left with 3 to the
2x plus 3 to the minus 2x

00:06:00.870 --> 00:06:02.340
is equal to b.

00:06:02.340 --> 00:06:03.390
But then we could
rewrite this.

00:06:03.390 --> 00:06:03.950
Think about this.

00:06:03.950 --> 00:06:08.060
3 to the 2x, that's the same
thing as 3 squared to the x.

00:06:08.060 --> 00:06:12.105
And this is the same thing as
3 to the minus 2 to the x is

00:06:12.105 --> 00:06:13.250
equal to b.

00:06:13.250 --> 00:06:16.960
And I think now bells are
ringing in your head.

00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:20.720
3 squared, that's the same thing
as 9 to the x plus-- I

00:06:20.720 --> 00:06:22.570
should do 3 squared
to the minus x.

00:06:22.570 --> 00:06:23.290
That's easier.

00:06:23.290 --> 00:06:26.450
Plus 9 to the minus
x is equal to b.

00:06:26.450 --> 00:06:28.870
So statement number one actually
reduced to what we

00:06:28.870 --> 00:06:30.170
